label.value: meiotic strand invasion involved in reciprocal meiotic recombination

value.value: The cell cycle process in which double strand breaks are formed and repaired through a double Holliday junction intermediate resulting in meiotic recombination. Meiotic recombination is the cell cycle process in which double strand breaks are formed and repaired through a double Holliday junction intermediate.

label.value: meiotic strand invasion involved in meiotic gene conversion

value.value: The cell cycle process in which double strand breaks are formed and repaired through a double Holliday junction intermediate resulting in meiotic recombination.

label.value: meiotic mismatch repair involved in meiotic gene conversion

value.value: A system for the identification and correction of base-base mismatches, small insertion-deletion loops, and regions of heterology that are present in duplex DNA formed with strands from two recombining molecules resulting in meiotic gene conversion. Meiotic gene conversion is the cell cycle process in which genetic information is transferred from one helix to another.

label.value: meiotic mismatch repair involved in reciprocal meiotic recombination

value.value: A system for the identification and correction of base-base mismatches, small insertion-deletion loops, and regions of heterology that are present in duplex DNA formed with strands from two recombining molecules resulting in meiotic recombination. Meiotic recombination is the cell cycle process in which double strand breaks are formed and repaired through a double Holliday junction intermediate.

label.value: meiotic DNA repair synthesis involved in reciprocal meiotic recombination

value.value: The synthesis of DNA proceeding from the broken 3' single-strand DNA end that uses the homologous intact duplex as the template resulting in meiotic recombination. Meiotic recombination is the cell cycle process in which double strand breaks are formed and repaired through a double Holliday junction intermediate.

label.value: meiotic DNA repair synthesis involved in meiotic gene conversion

value.value: The synthesis of DNA proceeding from the broken 3' single-strand DNA end that uses the homologous intact duplex as the template resulting in meiotic gene conversion. Meiotic gene conversion is the cell cycle process in which genetic information is transferred from one helix to another.

label.value: meiotic DNA double-strand break formation involved in reciprocal meiotic recombination

value.value: The cell cycle process in which double-strand breaks are generated at defined hotspots throughout the genome during meiosis I resulting in meiotic recombination. Meiotic recombination is the cell cycle process in which double strand breaks are formed and repaired through a double Holliday junction intermediate.

label.value: meiotic DNA double-strand break formation involved in meiotic gene conversion

value.value: The cell cycle process in which double-strand breaks are generated at defined hotspots throughout the genome during meiosis I resulting in meiotic gene conversion. Meiotic gene conversion is the cell cycle process in which genetic information is transferred from one helix to another.

label.value: proboscis morphogenesis, labial disc-derived

value.value: The process in which the anatomical structures of the proboscis that are derived from the labial disc are generated and organized.

label.value: proboscis morphogenesis, eye-antennal disc-derived

value.value: The process in which the anatomical structures of the proboscis that are derived from the eye-antennal disc are generated and organized.

label.value: proboscis morphogenesis, clypeo-labral disc-derived

value.value: The process in which the anatomical structures of the proboscis that are derived from the clypeo-labral disc are generated and organized.

label.value: clathrin coating of Golgi vesicle, plasma membrane to endosome targeting

value.value: The addition of clathrin and adaptor proteins to Golgi membranes during the formation of transport vesicles that will move from the plasma membrane to the endosome, forming a vesicle coat.

label.value: clathrin coating of Golgi vesicle, trans-Golgi to endosome targeting

value.value: The addition of clathrin and adaptor proteins to Golgi membranes during the formation of transport vesicles that will move from the trans-Golgi to the endosome, forming a vesicle coat.

label.value: COPI coating of Golgi vesicle, inter-Golgi cisterna

value.value: The addition of COPI proteins and adaptor proteins to Golgi membranes during the formation of inter-Golgi cisterna transport vesicles, forming a vesicle coat.

label.value: COPI coating of Golgi vesicle, cis-Golgi to rough ER

value.value: The addition of COPI proteins and adaptor proteins to Golgi membranes during the formation of cis-Golgi to rough ER transport vesicles, forming a vesicle coat.

label.value: meiotic sister chromatid cohesion involved in meiosis I

value.value: The cell cycle process in which sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome are joined along the entire length of the chromosome during meiosis I.

label.value: meiotic sister chromatid cohesion involved in meiosis II

value.value: The cell cycle process in which sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome are joined along the entire length of the chromosome during meiosis II.

label.value: DNA double-strand break processing involved in repair via synthesis-dependent strand annealing

value.value: The 5' to 3' exonucleolytic resection of the DNA at the site of the break to form a 3' single-strand DNA overhang that results in the repair of a double strand break via synthesis-dependent strand annealing.

label.value: DNA double-strand break processing involved in repair via single-strand annealing

value.value: The 5' to 3' exonucleolytic resection of the DNA at the site of the break to form a 3' single-strand DNA overhang that results in the repair of a double strand break via single-strand annealing.

label.value: regulation of mRNA export from nucleus

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of mRNA from the nucleus to the cytoplasm.

label.value: regulation of dolichol biosynthetic process

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of dolichol biosynthesis. Dolichol biosynthesis consists of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of dolichols, any 2,3-dihydropolyprenol derived from four or more linked isoprene units.

label.value: regulation of ubiquinone biosynthetic process

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of ubiquinone biosynthesis. Ubiquinone biosynthesis consists of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of ubiquinone, a lipid-soluble electron-transporting coenzyme.

label.value: regulation of multivesicular body size

value.value: Any process that modulates the volume of a multivesicular body, a type of late endosome in which regions of the limiting endosomal membrane invaginate to form internal vesicles.

label.value: regulation of multivesicular body size involved in endosome transport

value.value: Any process that modulates the volume of a multivesicular body as part of the directed movement of substances from endosomes to lysosomes or vacuoles.

label.value: regulation of multivesicular body size involved in ubiquitin-dependent protein catabolism

value.value: Any process that modulates the volume of a multivesicular body as part of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a protein or peptide covalently tagged with ubiquitin.

label.value: regulation of peptidyl-threonine phosphorylation

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of peptidyl-threonine phosphorylation. Peptidyl-threonine phosphorylation is the phosphorylation of peptidyl-threonine to form peptidyl-O-phospho-L-threonine.

label.value: positive regulation of peptidyl-threonine phosphorylation

value.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of peptidyl-threonine phosphorylation. Peptidyl-threonine phosphorylation is the phosphorylation of peptidyl-threonine to form peptidyl-O-phospho-L-threonine.

label.value: negative regulation of peptidyl-threonine phosphorylation

value.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of peptidyl-threonine phosphorylation. Peptidyl-threonine phosphorylation is the phosphorylation of peptidyl-threonine to form peptidyl-O-phospho-L-threonine.

label.value: regulation of tumor necrosis factor-mediated signaling pathway

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate or extent of the tumor necrosis factor-mediated signaling pathway. The tumor necrosis factor-mediated signaling pathway is the series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of tumor necrosis factor binding to a cell surface receptor.

label.value: negative regulation of tumor necrosis factor-mediated signaling pathway

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate or extent of the tumor necrosis factor-mediated signaling pathway. The tumor necrosis factor-mediated signaling pathway is the series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of tumor necrosis factor binding to a cell surface receptor.

label.value: regulation of synaptic vesicle priming

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of synaptic vesicle priming. Synaptic vesicle priming is the formation of SNARE-containing complexes, bringing synaptic vesicle membrane and plasma membranes into close proximity and thereby facilitating membrane fusion.

label.value: positive regulation of synaptic vesicle priming

value.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of synaptic vesicle priming. Synaptic vesicle priming is the formation of SNARE-containing complexes, bringing synaptic vesicle membrane and plasma membranes into close proximity and thereby facilitating membrane fusion.

label.value: negative regulation of synaptic vesicle priming

value.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of synaptic vesicle priming. Synaptic vesicle priming is the formation of SNARE-containing complexes, bringing synaptic vesicle membrane and plasma membranes into close proximity and thereby facilitating membrane fusion.

label.value: regulation of cell-substrate adhesion

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell-substrate adhesion. Cell-substrate adhesion is the attachment of a cell to the underlying substrate via adhesion molecules.

label.value: positive regulation of cell-substrate adhesion

value.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of cell-substrate adhesion. Cell-substrate adhesion is the attachment of a cell to the underlying substrate via adhesion molecules.

label.value: negative regulation of cell-substrate adhesion

value.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of cell-substrate adhesion. Cell-substrate adhesion is the attachment of a cell to the underlying substrate via adhesion molecules.

label.value: neuropeptide catabolic process

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of neuropeptides. Neuropeptides are signaling peptides that travel across a synaptic junction.

label.value: substance P catabolic process

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of the neuropeptide substance P.

label.value: bradykinin catabolic process

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of the peptide bradykinin.

label.value: calcitonin catabolic process

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of the peptide calcitonin.

label.value: regulation of hormone levels

value.value: Any process that modulates the levels of hormone within an organism or a tissue. A hormone is any substance formed in very small amounts in one specialized organ or group of cells and carried (sometimes in the bloodstream) to another organ or group of cells in the same organism, upon which it has a specific regulatory action.

label.value: T cell chemotaxis

value.value: The directed movement of a T cell in response to an external stimulus. A T cell is a type of lymphocyte whose defining characteristic is the expression of a T cell receptor complex.

label.value: regulation of T cell chemotaxis

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of T cell chemotaxis. T cell chemotaxis is the directed movement of a T cell in response to an external stimulus.

label.value: positive regulation of T cell chemotaxis

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of T cell chemotaxis. T cell chemotaxis is the directed movement of a T cell in response to an external stimulus.

label.value: regulation of mitochondrion organization

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a process involved in the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a mitochondrion.

label.value: regulation of centrosome duplication

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of centrosome duplication. Centrosome duplication is the replication of a centrosome, a structure comprised of a pair of centrioles and peri-centriolar material from which a microtubule spindle apparatus is organized.

label.value: positive regulation of centrosome duplication

value.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of centrosome duplication. Centrosome duplication is the replication of a centrosome, a structure comprised of a pair of centrioles and peri-centriolar material from which a microtubule spindle apparatus is organized.

label.value: negative regulation of centrosome duplication

value.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of centrosome duplication. Centrosome duplication is the replication of a centrosome, a structure comprised of a pair of centrioles and peri-centriolar material from which a microtubule spindle apparatus is organized.

label.value: regulation of D-glucose transmembrane transport

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of glucose transport across a membrane. Glucose transport is the directed movement of the hexose monosaccharide glucose into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label.value: positive regulation of D-glucose transmembrane transport

value.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of glucose transport across a membrane. Glucose transport is the directed movement of the hexose monosaccharide glucose into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.
